많이 a lot
진구가 많아 있어요 I have a lot of friends
한국에 많이  갔어요 I went to Korea a lot
파티에 진구가 많이 왔어요 Many friends came to the party
You can add 같이 (verb) to do a (verb) together
(somebody) 하고 같이 (verb) : to do a (verb) together with someone
친구와 갔어요 I went with a friend ( 와/ 과) If the person you are doing something with has a 받침 then use 과 and if not use 와
친구하고 갔어요 You can also use 하고 which never changes and is always the same if or if not there is a 받침
랑 / 이람 If the person you are doing something with has a 받침 use 어람 and if not use 랑
친구랑 갔어요 I went with a friend
----- ------ ----- ----- ------ 
에둥생이 랑 같이 갔어요 I went together with my younger sister
누나하고 영국에 갈 거예요 I will go to England with my older sister
부모님하고 식당에 갔어요 I went to a restaurant with my parents
유월에 친구랑 태국에 갈 거예요 I will go to Thailand with a friend in June
와/과, 하고, 랑 / 이랑 also mean "and"
김밥하고 김치가 맛있어요
개랑 고양이가 너무 귀여워요 Dogs and cats are very cute
조지 씨하고 김민수 씨하고 가게에 같이 갈 거예요 I will go to the store (together) with George and Minsu Kim 

